<subSubSection id="87B46525FFEDFFF7FF6953DCFB07295C" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEDFFF7FF6953DCFECE2A91" blockId="18.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">
<heading id="945981C2FFEDFFF7FF6953DCFECE2A91" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEDFFF7FF6953DCFECE2A91" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEDFFF7FF6953F3FB07295C" blockId="18.[188,1399,447,615]" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFEDFFF7FEFE538CFE732AE2" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[298,395,448,473]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEDFFF7FEFE538CFE732AE2" box="[298,395,448,473]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">N. maisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFEDFFF7FE46538CFE142AE1" box="[402,492,448,474]" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are distinguished from all congeners by the palps with TBE bifid, with longer branch filiform and the other small and thorn-like (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEDFFF7FCD953AEFCA72AC6" box="[781,863,482,509]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[189,1388,304,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-15@21.[189,1399,287,1685]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Neostasina maisi sp. nov., A−D: holotype, ♂ (MNHNCu), E−F: paratype, ♀ (MNHNCu). A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. TBE, detail, ventral view. E. Epigyne, dorsal view. F. Vulva, ventral view. G. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; C = conductor; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MA=median apophysis; MS = median septum; pt = tegular protrusion; SP = spermathecae; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA=ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607940/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
B−C). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFEDFFF7FB2753AFFA8F2AC7" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[1267,1399,482,508]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baoruco">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEDFFF7FB2753AFFA8F2AC7" box="[1267,1399,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">N. baoruco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB3F4B5FFFEDFFF7FF13504AFE19291B" author="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G." box="[199,481,518,544]" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" pagination="301 - 344" refId="ref12419" refString="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G. 2016. Neostasina gen. nov., a new genus of huntsman spiders from the Neotropical region (Araneae, Sparassidae, Sparianthinae). Zootaxa 4079: 301 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4079.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Rheims &amp; Alayón 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 23) by the epigyne with ar divided and MS roughly triangular. They are distinguished from the latter species by the spermathecae anteriorly globose with smooth lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEDFFF7FF105000FEDF295D" box="[196,295,588,614]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[189,1388,304,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-15@21.[189,1399,287,1685]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Neostasina maisi sp. nov., A−D: holotype, ♂ (MNHNCu), E−F: paratype, ♀ (MNHNCu). A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. TBE, detail, ventral view. E. Epigyne, dorsal view. F. Vulva, ventral view. G. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; C = conductor; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MA=median apophysis; MS = median septum; pt = tegular protrusion; SP = spermathecae; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA=ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607940/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">Fig 11A</figureCitation>
) (inverted U-shaped with outer lateral margins bearing indentations in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFEDFFF7FBBE5001FB16295D" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[1130,1262,588,614]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baoruco">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEDFFF7FBBE5001FB16295D" box="[1130,1262,588,614]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="184">N. baoruco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
